        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Hardened runtime/plugin schema and metadata boundaries so malformed or unreadable synthetic plugin data is quarantined, omitted, or treated as absent instead of crashing assistant startup, doctor/setup flows, provider selection, channel authorization, Codex app-server routing, gateway startup planning, or SDK helper APIs.\n- Kept test fixtures synthetic: current test content uses `fuzzplugin`, `mockplugin`, and `fuzz_move_*` names rather than the reported third-party plugin name.\n- Added follow-up hardening for Plugin SDK SSRF/private-network config reads, provider/config type-safety drift, Codex URL-backed image preservation, embedded-agent compaction schema-quarantine fixtures, provider wizard setup/model-picker metadata reads, and manifest alias/channel reads used by gateway startup planning.\n- Bound provider wizard setup/model-picker metadata reads so unreadable provider/method wizard fields cannot crash setup choices; readable sibling providers/methods still appear, onboarding scopes are copied without trusting array methods, and the provider receiver is preserved for model-selected hooks.\n- Bound gateway startup manifest reads so unreadable manifest `plugins`, `channels`, `providers`, activation lists, contracts, setup provider ids, CLI backends, model-catalog keys, or legacy aliases cannot crash plugin id normalization or startup planning; readable sibling manifest metadata still resolves.\n- Out of scope: changing global plugin materialization policy or rejecting valid non-Codex schemas outside the Codex/doctor projection path.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nNo linked closing issue.\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nNo linked related issue.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nMaintainer-directed hardening/debugging work.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: malformed runtime plugin tool schemas and hostile plugin/config/provider/manifest metadata can crash or widen decisions before normal OpenClaw diagnostics, setup, provider routing, gateway startup planning, or Codex app-server handling complete.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`; broad remote validation on direct AWS Crabbox Linux runners because Blacksmith Testbox auth was unavailable in this shell.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Direct pre/post `tsx` repro for an unreadable synthetic provider auth-method `wizard` getter: before fix it threw; after fix the readable `mockplugin` wizard option was returned.\n- Direct pre/post `tsx` repro for unreadable synthetic manifest `channels` metadata: before fix gateway startup planning threw inside plugin-id alias normalization; after fix readable `mockplugin` channel metadata was returned and unreadable `fuzzplugin` metadata was skipped.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/channel-plugin-ids.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 109 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 26 tests after latest rebase)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/provider-wizard.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 10 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugin-sdk/ssrf-policy.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 48 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/elevenlabs/speech-provider.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 6 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (2 projects / 110 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/codex/src/app-server/image-payload-sanitizer.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 7 tests)\n- Focused affected batches for manifest/tool availability, provider auth/onboarding, channel/config fixtures, and fuzz guard type/lint drift (largest reruns: 11 files / 180 tests; 16 files / 323 tests; 8 files / 113 tests)\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check` and `node_modules/.bin/oxlint` on the latest touched file sets\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base refs/remotes/origin/main`\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --idle-timeout 90m --ttl 240m --timing-json --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Final branch autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings after rebasing onto current `origin/main`.\n- Latest focused proof after rebase to `b0e9569ebd`: `channel-plugin-ids.test.ts` passed 1 file / 109 tests; `plugin-registry.test.ts` passed 1 file / 26 tests; oxfmt, oxlint, `git diff --check`, and added-line scrub passed.\n- AWS Crabbox changed gate after the provider-wizard slice: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_991a8c29acdf`, run `run_41811346ac17`, command `pnpm check:changed`, exit 0 on base `8e806e9125`.\n- Earlier AWS Crabbox changed gate for the branch: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_52b1fe398bd3`, run `run_c85914033aaa`, command `pnpm check:changed`, exit 0 over core, coreTests, extensions, and extensionTests.\n- Final rebase state: branch rebased onto `origin/main` at `b0e9569ebd`; latest main drift had zero touched-path overlap with this branch.\n- Current branch head after rebase/push: `6ed90bbda930d2088b8e89fd5346cc16aabb7cae`.\n- Current test content scrub: no reported third-party plugin name remains in repo test/source/docs content checked for this branch.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- Hostile synthetic config/schema/provider/manifest inputs are bounded at the relevant owner boundary instead of throwing raw getter/enumeration/serialization errors.\n- Provider wizard setup choices skip unreadable provider/auth-method metadata while preserving readable sibling options and receiver-sensitive hooks.\n- Gateway startup planning skips unreadable manifest alias/channel lists while preserving readable sibling channel ownership and plugin-id aliases.\n- Manifest tool availability remains fail-closed when config-signal metadata is unreadable or malformed.\n- Valid URL-backed Codex image blocks remain preserved while invalid inline image payloads are still replaced with the existing omitted-image text.\n- Embedded-agent schema-quarantine and plugin fixtures use synthetic names and pass focused proof.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox was not run because `blacksmith auth login` is required in this shell; direct AWS Crabbox was used for broad remote gates.\n- After the latest green AWS gate, `origin/main` advanced multiple times. Overlap at `9a7014ac38` was in `src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts`; the branch rebased cleanly and focused overlap proof passed. The final advance to `b0e9569ebd` had zero touched-path overlap, so the branch rebased cleanly and only cheap post-rebase sanity was rerun per repo policy.\n- GitHub PR checks are expected to queue on the pushed head.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo new config surface. Existing malformed/unreadable config or manifest inputs now fail closed or resolve as absent at bounded reads.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes. Malformed or unreadable tool/provider/plugin metadata is rejected, omitted, or quarantined earlier instead of crashing runtime paths or broadening access.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nOverly strict sanitation could omit a valid schema, provider hint, setup choice, channel allowlist, manifest alias, or Codex payload field.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nThe changes preserve readable sibling entries, keep valid URL-backed and inline image forms covered by tests, retain receiver-sensitive provider hooks, keep readable manifest aliases/channels resolving, and use focused regressions plus broad AWS `check:changed` gates across core and extension type/lint/guard lanes.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\nReview the draft PR at head `6ed90bbda930d2088b8e89fd5346cc16aabb7cae`.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\nGitHub CI is queued/running after the force-push. No local actionable autoreview findings remain.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\nLocal autoreview findings were addressed, including the Codex URL-backed image-block preservation regression and the provider wizard receiver regression found before commit.\n",
